       cascade order wins) ──────────────────────────────────────────── */

:root[data-theme="t3-light"] {
  color-scheme: light;
  /* Mirrors existing :root light defaults; explicit for stability */
  --background: var(--color-white);
  --foreground: var(--color-neutral-800);
  --card: var(--color-white);
  --card-foreground: var(--color-neutral-800);
  --popover: var(--color-white);
  --popover-foreground: var(--color-neutral-800);
  --primary: oklch(0.488 0.217 264);
  --primary-foreground: var(--color-white);
  --secondary: --alpha(var(--color-black) / 4%);
  --secondary-foreground: var(--color-neutral-800);
  --muted: --alpha(var(--color-black) / 4%);
  --muted-foreground: color-mix(in srgb, var(--color-neutral-500) 90%, var(--color-black));
  --accent: --alpha(var(--color-black) / 4%);
  --accent-foreground: var(--color-neutral-800);
  --destructive: var(--color-red-500);
  --destructive-foreground: var(--color-red-700);
  --border: --alpha(var(--color-black) / 8%);
  --input: --alpha(var(--color-black) / 10%);
  --ring: oklch(0.488 0.217 264);
  --info: var(--color-blue-500);
  --info-foreground: var(--color-blue-700);
  --success: var(--color-emerald-500);
  --success-foreground: var(--color-emerald-700);
  --warning: var(--color-amber-500);
  --warning-foreground: var(--color-amber-700);
  /* Theme-specific surface tokens */
  --theme-sidebar: var(--color-neutral-50);
  --theme-editor: var(--color-white);
  --theme-terminal: var(--color-neutral-50);
  --theme-status-bar: var(--color-neutral-100);
}

:root[data-theme="t3-dark"] {
  color-scheme: dark;
  /* Mirrors existing @variant dark values */
  --background: color-mix(in srgb, var(--color-neutral-950) 95%, var(--color-white));
  --foreground: var(--color-neutral-100);
  --card: color-mix(in srgb, var(--background) 98%, var(--color-white));
  --card-foreground: var(--color-neutral-100);
  --popover: color-mix(in srgb, var(--background) 98%, var(--color-white));
  --popover-foreground: var(--color-neutral-100);
  --primary: oklch(0.588 0.217 264);
  --primary-foreground: var(--color-white);
  --secondary: --alpha(var(--color-white) / 4%);
  --secondary-foreground: var(--color-neutral-100);
  --muted: --alpha(var(--color-white) / 4%);
  --muted-foreground: color-mix(in srgb, var(--color-neutral-500) 90%, var(--color-white));
  --accent: --alpha(var(--color-white) / 4%);
  --accent-foreground: var(--color-neutral-100);
  --destructive: color-mix(in srgb, var(--color-red-500) 90%, var(--color-white));
  --destructive-foreground: var(--color-red-400);
  --border: --alpha(var(--color-white) / 6%);
  --input: --alpha(var(--color-white) / 8%);
  --ring: oklch(0.588 0.217 264);
  --info: var(--color-blue-500);
  --info-foreground: var(--color-blue-400);
  --success: var(--color-emerald-500);
  --success-foreground: var(--color-emerald-400);
  --warning: var(--color-amber-500);
  --warning-foreground: var(--color-amber-400);
  /* Theme-specific surface tokens */
  --theme-sidebar: color-mix(in srgb, var(--color-neutral-950) 98%, var(--color-white));
  --theme-editor: color-mix(in srgb, var(--color-neutral-950) 95%, var(--color-white));
  --theme-terminal: color-mix(in srgb, var(--color-neutral-950) 98%, var(--color-white));
  --theme-status-bar: color-mix(in srgb, var(--color-neutral-900) 80%, var(--color-neutral-950));
}

:root[data-theme="t3-midnight"] {
  color-scheme: dark;
  /* Deeper blue-black variant */
  --background: #080c14;
  --foreground: #c9d4e8;
  --card: #0c1120;
  --card-foreground: #c9d4e8;
  --popover: #0c1120;
  --popover-foreground: #c9d4e8;
  --primary: oklch(0.62 0.2 245);
  --primary-foreground: var(--color-white);
  --secondary: oklch(0.2 0.04 245 / 30%);
  --secondary-foreground: #c9d4e8;
  --muted: oklch(0.2 0.04 245 / 30%);
  --muted-foreground: #7f9cbf;
  --accent: oklch(0.2 0.04 245 / 40%);
  --accent-foreground: #c9d4e8;
  --destructive: #e05a6a;
  --destructive-foreground: #fca5b3;
  --border: oklch(0.4 0.06 245 / 18%);
  --input: oklch(0.4 0.06 245 / 22%);
  --ring: oklch(0.62 0.2 245);
  --info: #60a5fa;
  --info-foreground: #93c5fd;
  --success: #34d399;
  --success-foreground: #6ee7b7;
  --warning: #fbbf24;
  --warning-foreground: #fcd34d;
  /* Theme-specific surface tokens */
  --theme-sidebar: #0c1222;
  --theme-editor: #080c14;
  --theme-terminal: #060a10;
  --theme-status-bar: #0f1926;
}
```

Also add `--theme-sidebar`, `--theme-editor`, `--theme-terminal`, `--theme-status-bar` to the base `:root {}` block (light defaults) so the vars are always defined.

### Step 7 — `apps/web/src/components/ThemeSelector.tsx` (NEW)

Imports: `BUILT_IN_THEMES` from `@t3tools/shared/theme`, `useTheme` from `../hooks/useTheme`.

Structure:
- `export function ThemeSelector()`
- `const { theme, setTheme } = useTheme()`
- `role="radiogroup"` wrapper div with `aria-label="Color theme"`
- Maps `BUILT_IN_THEMES` → a `<button>` per theme styled to match the existing settings radio-button pattern:
  - Selected: `border-primary/60 bg-primary/8 text-foreground`
  - Unselected: `border-border bg-background text-muted-foreground hover:bg-accent`
- Swatch preview inside each button: a small `div` (e.g. `h-8 w-full rounded-md`) split into 3 vertical strips using inline `style={{ background }}` from `t.colors.sidebar`, `t.colors.editor`, `t.colors.accent` — giving a visual mini-preview of the color scheme.
- Below swatch: `<span className="text-sm font-medium">{t.label}</span>` and `<span className="text-xs">{t.description}</span>`.
- No new dependencies — all Tailwind utility classes already in use.

### Step 8 — `apps/web/src/routes/_chat.settings.tsx` (MODIFY)

1. Remove: `THEME_OPTIONS` const (lines 25–41).
2. Add import: `import { ThemeSelector } from "../components/ThemeSelector"`.
3. In `SettingsRouteView`: drop `theme` and `setTheme` from the `useTheme()` destructure (keep `resolvedTheme` only if the "Active theme" line is retained, otherwise remove `useTheme` call entirely since `ThemeSelector` handles it).
4. Replace the entire `<div role="radiogroup" ...>{THEME_OPTIONS.map(...)}</div>` JSX block with `<ThemeSelector />`.
5. Update the section description: `"Choose how T3 Code handles light and dark mode."` → `"Choose your color theme."`.
6. The `<p>Active theme: {resolvedTheme}</p>` line can be kept (shows "light" or "dark") or removed.

---

## Critical Files

| File | Action |
|---|---|
| `packages/shared/src/theme.ts` | **CREATE** |
| `packages/shared/package.json` | **MODIFY** — add `./theme` export |
| `apps/web/src/hooks/useTheme.ts` | **REWRITE** |
| `apps/web/src/components/ThemeProvider.tsx` | **CREATE** |
| `apps/web/src/components/ThemeSelector.tsx` | **CREATE** |
| `apps/web/src/routes/__root.tsx` | **MODIFY** — add `<ThemeProvider>` wrapper |
| `apps/web/src/routes/_chat.settings.tsx` | **MODIFY** — replace Appearance section |
| `apps/web/src/index.css` | **MODIFY** — append 3 theme blocks + base vars |

**Unchanged** (no edits needed):
- `DiffWorkerPoolProvider.tsx`, `DiffPanel.tsx`, `ChatMarkdown.tsx`, `ChatView.tsx` (all use `resolvedTheme` only)
- `ThreadTerminalDrawer.tsx` (uses `classList.contains("dark")` which is still managed)
- `packages/contracts/` (schema-only; theme data lives in shared)

---

## Verification

1. **`bun typecheck`** in `packages/shared` — confirms `./theme` subpath resolves and `Theme` types are valid.
2. **`bun typecheck`** in `apps/web` — confirms updated `useTheme` return type satisfies all callers; `ThemeSelector` and `ThemeProvider` compile cleanly.
3. **`bun lint`** in root — no unused imports, no barrel violations.
4. **Flash test**: hard-refresh with `t3code:theme = "t3-midnight"` in localStorage. Page should load dark immediately (module-level `applyTheme` fires before React paint).
5. **Theme switching**: click each card in Settings → Appearance. Verify `html[data-theme]` attribute and `.dark` class update; background/foreground/accent CSS vars change visibly.
6. **Tailwind dark: utilities**: Sidebar status pills (e.g. `dark:text-sky-300/80`) should render correctly in dark themes — depends on `.dark` class which is preserved.
7. **Diff panel**: switch themes; diff surfaces pick up `resolvedTheme` → `resolveDiffThemeName` → correct pierre-light/dark theme.
8. **Terminal theming**: open terminal in dark vs light theme; `terminalThemeFromApp()` in `ThreadTerminalDrawer` reads `classList.contains("dark")` — confirms correct xterm.js palette.
9. **Persistence + migration**: set `t3code:theme = "dark"` → reload → confirm migrates to `"t3-dark"` and UI shows T3 Dark selected.
10. **Cross-tab sync**: change theme in tab A; tab B's storage event fires and applies the new theme without reload.

